[section#exec.schedule.from
    [`execution::schedule_from]
]

[para]
[:en] The name [`schedule_from] denotes a customization point object.
[:zh_CN] 名字 [`schedule_from] 表示一个定制化点对象。

[:en] For some subexpression [`sndr], if [`decltype((sndr))] does not satisfy
[`:c sender], [`schedule_from(sndr)] is ill-formed.
[:zh_CN] 对于某个子表达式 [`sndr]，如果 [`decltype((sndr))] 不满足 [`:c sender]，
则 [`schedule_from(sndr)] 非良构。

[:en] Otherwise, the expression [`schedule_from(sndr)] is expression-equivalent to
[`[*make-sender](schedule_from, {}, sndr)].
[:zh_CN] 否则，表达式 [`schedule_from(sndr)] 按表达式等价于 [`[*make-sender](schedule_from, {}, sndr)]。

[begin:note]
[:en] [`schedule_from] is used by schedulers to control
how to transition off of their schedulers[='] associated execution contexts.
[:zh_CN] 调度器利用 [`schedule_from] 来控制如何从它们关联的执行上下文中转移。
[end:note]
